metadata.title: Piper PA-18 Super Cub
aws::graph::propositions: Military Operators of Piper PA-18 Super Cub
The Argentine Air Force operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Argentine National Gendarmerie operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Austrian Air Force operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Belgian Army operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Cyprus Air Command operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Federal German Luftwaffe operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Greek Army operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Imperial Iranian Air Force operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Italian Army operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Israeli Air Force operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Japan Ground Self-Defense Force operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Force Aérienne Katangaise operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
Force Aérienne Katangaise was the air force of Katanga.
The Netherlands Air Force operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Nicaraguan Air Force operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Royal Norwegian Air Force operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Portuguese Army operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Portuguese Air Force operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Swedish Army operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Swiss Air Force operated the Piper PA-18 Super Cub.
The Swiss Air Force operated 4 PA-18-150 Super Cubs.
The Swiss Air Force designated the PA-18-150 Super Cubs as V-653 to V-656.
The Swiss Air Force operated the PA-18-150 Super Cubs from 1964 to 1975.
The Swiss Air Force's V-654 Super Cub later became registered as HB-PAV.
The Swiss Air Force's V-655 Super Cub later became registered as HB-PAW.
The Swiss Air Force's V-656 Super Cub later became registered as HB-PAX.
